QUESTION 15 - THEORETICAL CALCULATION

Given:

F1 = 0.05P1² + 20P1 + 800

F2 = 0.06P2² + 15P2 + 1000

Total Load Demand

P1 + P2 = 150 MW

--------------------------------------------------

1. Incremental Cost of Generator 1

dF1/dP1

= 0.1P1 + 20

--------------------------------------------------

2. Incremental Cost of Generator 2

dF2/dP2

= 0.12P2 + 15

--------------------------------------------------

3. Economic Dispatch Condition

dF1/dP1 = dF2/dP2

0.1P1 + 20

=

0.12P2 + 15

--------------------------------------------------

4. Rearranging

0.1P1 - 0.12P2 = -5

--------------------------------------------------

5. Power Balance Equation

P1 + P2 = 150

--------------------------------------------------

6. Multiply Equation (5) by 0.12

0.12P1 + 0.12P2 = 18

--------------------------------------------------

7. Add Equations

(0.1P1 - 0.12P2)

+

(0.12P1 + 0.12P2)

=

-5 + 18

0.22P1 = 13

P1 = 13/0.22

P1 = 59.09 MW

--------------------------------------------------

8. Substitute in Power Balance Equation

59.09 + P2 = 150

P2 = 150 - 59.09

P2 = 90.91 MW

--------------------------------------------------

RESULT

Generator 1 Output

P1 = 59.09 MW

Generator 2 Output

P2 = 90.91 MW
